window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Secrets and rage can get under the skin in an unsettling short story by Ivy Pochoda, award-winning author of <i>Sing Her Down</i> and <i>These Women</i>.</p> <p>Swan is a tattoo artist new to a community in the California desert when a mourning desert dweller named Kurt requests a tribute tattoo to his dead wife. Swan agrees, but the locals warn her: don’t indulge Kurt in his tragic memories. No wonder. As Kurt returns for more tattoos, the truth about his wife’s death begins to emerge in the ink. And it isn’t pretty.</p> <p><i>Ivy Pochoda’s </i>Jackrabbit Skin<i> is part of </i>Never Tell<i>, a heart-pounding collection of stories about secrets, lies, and mind games. They can be read or listened to in one sitting. Just keep the endings to yourself.</i></p>"; 
